```
Then use `filtered` instead of `allMatches` for the rest of the function. Note: calling urlMatchesPatterns here with just the exclude patterns as the include patterns (not the 3-arg version) since we want to check if the URL matches ANY exclude pattern.

Actually, simpler: just use matchPattern directly or a helper. The key insight is that `urlMatchesPatterns(url, excludePatterns)` (the 2-arg version, treating excludePatterns as include patterns) tells us if the URL matches an exclude pattern. So:
```typescript
const filtered = excludePatterns.length > 0
  ? allMatches.filter(tab => !tab.url || !urlMatchesPatterns(tab.url, excludePatterns))
  : allMatches;
```

