Actually, queryMatchingTabIds currently only returns tab IDs (numbers), not full tab objects. It would need to either return tab objects or look up URLs. Check the function signature and callers. The callers (injectPluginIntoMatchingTabs, cleanupAdaptersInMatchingTabs, reinjectStoredPlugins) all pass urlPatterns from PluginMeta. The simplest approach: change queryMatchingTabIds to accept excludePatterns and use chrome.tabs.get() to check URLs before including IDs, OR change to return chrome.tabs.Tab[] like findAllMatchingTabs does.

Simplest approach: use `chrome.tabs.query` results which include `.url`, then post-filter before extracting IDs:
```typescript
const queryMatchingTabIds = async (urlPatterns: string[], excludePatterns?: string[]): Promise<number[]> => {
  const seen = new Set<number>();
  const ids: number[] = [];
  for (const pattern of urlPatterns) {
    let tabs: chrome.tabs.Tab[];
    try { tabs = await chrome.tabs.query({ url: pattern }); } catch { continue; }
    for (const tab of tabs) {
      if (tab.id !== undefined && !seen.has(tab.id)) {
        if (excludePatterns && excludePatterns.length > 0 && tab.url && urlMatchesPatterns(tab.url, excludePatterns)) continue;
        seen.add(tab.id);
        ids.push(tab.id);
      }
    }
  }
  return ids;
};
```
Update all callers to pass excludePatterns.

